1️⃣ Email Ingestion Service
🎯 Purpose

Safely and efficiently fetch emails from the user’s inbox and turn them into immutable internal messages.

📥 Inputs

OAuth credentials (read-only)

User-defined filters (senders, keywords, date range)

Sync schedule (daily)

📤 Outputs

IngestedEmail records (raw but sanitized)

Metadata (messageId, threadId, timestamp)

✅ Responsibilities

Connect to Gmail API (read-only)

Fetch only new or changed emails

Apply coarse filtering (sender, subject, labels)

Strip HTML → plain text

Encrypt sensitive fields

Assign internal IDs

Persist temporarily

❌ Must NOT

Classify emails

Extract financial data

Apply business rules

Store raw email long-term

Make assumptions about content

🧠 Design Notes

Idempotent ingestion (no duplicates)

Stateless execution where possible

Supports reprocessing

Hard retention limit (e.g., 72h)

2️⃣ Rules Engine
🎯 Purpose

Decide what should happen next with an ingested email.

📥 Inputs

IngestedEmail

User preferences

System rules

📤 Outputs

Processing directives:

Ignore

Classify

Extract

Flag for review

✅ Responsibilities

Apply deterministic rules

Enforce compliance constraints

Route emails to next step

Handle allowlists / blocklists

Control cost (AI usage gating)

❌ Must NOT

Call AI models

Modify data

Extract values

Store results

🧠 Design Notes

Rule definitions should be declarative

Version rules over time

Rules > ML when possible

Log decisions for auditability

3️⃣ Classification Service
🎯 Purpose

Determine what kind of email this is.

📥 Inputs

Clean email text

Metadata

📤 Outputs

Classification label:

Financial

Non-financial

Unknown

Confidence score

Category (payment, transfer, receipt, invoice, etc.)

✅ Responsibilities

Detect financial relevance

Categorize transaction type

Provide confidence

Be fast and cheap

❌ Must NOT

Extract specific values

Apply business logic

Persist final records

🧠 Design Notes

Lightweight ML / AI or heuristics

Fail-safe to “unknown”

No irreversible decisions

Cache classification results

4️⃣ Extraction Service
🎯 Purpose

Extract candidate financial data from classified emails.

📥 Inputs

Classified email

Email text

Extraction schema

📤 Outputs

Candidate fields:

Amount

Currency

Date

Merchant

Reference IDs

Confidence per field

✅ Responsibilities

Use AI / LLMs carefully

Return structured output

Handle ambiguous data

Highlight uncertainties

Support multiple templates

❌ Must NOT

Normalize data

Decide correctness

Auto-confirm anything

Persist confirmed records

🧠 Design Notes

Strict output schema (JSON)

Prompt versioning

Cost & token controls

Deterministic retry strategy

5️⃣ Normalization Layer
🎯 Purpose

Convert extracted candidates into consistent, comparable financial data.

📥 Inputs

Extracted candidate data

User locale

Currency rules

📤 Outputs

Normalized financial record (draft)

Validation errors (if any)

✅ Responsibilities

Normalize currencies

Standardize dates (UTC)

Clean merchant names

Validate amounts

Apply formatting rules

Prepare data for confirmation UI

❌ Must NOT

Change original meaning

Guess missing data

Persist without confirmation

Apply business decisions

🧠 Design Notes

Pure, deterministic logic

No external calls

Easily testable

Re-runnable

🔄 End-to-End Flow Summary
Email Ingestion
 → Rules Engine
   → Classification
     → Extraction
       → Normalization
         → User Confirmation


Each component:

Does one thing

Can be replaced independently

Is auditable

Supports compliance

🏁 Key Architectural Principle

Rules decide, AI suggests, users confirm.

This keeps:

Costs down

Trust high

Regulators happy

Architecture clean